<!-- Fiber / OTDR -->
<div id="m1-fiber" class="stab-page">
<div class="grid">
<div class="card">
<h3>Fiber Link Budget</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> A link budget is a balance sheet for light. You start with transmit power, subtract every loss between Tx and Rx (fiber attenuation, connector loss, splice loss, any splitters), and the result must be above your receiver's sensitivity threshold.
<div class="mth">Power_Rx = P_Tx − Loss_fiber − Loss_connectors − Loss_splices − margin
Loss_fiber  = length_km × attenuation_dB/km
Loss_conn   = n_connectors × 0.5 dB (typical)
Loss_splice = n_splices × 0.1 dB (fusion) or × 0.3 dB (mech)
System margin: ≥ 3 dB recommended</div></div>
<div class="field"><label>Transmit power (dBm)</label><input type="number" id="fb-tx" placeholder="e.g. 0" oninput="calcFB()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Receiver sensitivity (dBm)</label><input type="number" id="fb-rx" placeholder="e.g. -24" oninput="calcFB()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Fiber length (km)</label><input type="number" id="fb-l" placeholder="e.g. 10" oninput="calcFB()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Fiber type / attenuation</label>
<select id="fb-atten" onchange="calcFB()">
<option value="0.4">SMF 1310nm — 0.4 dB/km</option>
<option value="0.25">SMF 1550nm — 0.25 dB/km</option>
<option value="3.5">OM1 MMF 850nm — 3.5 dB/km</option>
<option value="2.5">OM3/OM4 MMF 850nm — 2.5 dB/km</option>
<option value="custom">Custom dB/km</option>
</select></div>
<div class="field"><label>Number of connectors</label><input type="number" id="fb-nc" value="2" min="0" oninput="calcFB()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Number of fusion splices</label><input type="number" id="fb-ns" value="0" min="0" oninput="calcFB()"></div>
<div id="fb-result" class="result"></div>
</div>
<div class="card">
<h3>OTDR Distance Calculator</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> OTDR measures round-trip travel time of light. To get distance, you need the Index of Refraction (IOR) for your fiber. Wrong IOR = wrong distance reading.
<div class="mth">d = (c × t) / (2 × IOR)
  c   = 299,792,458 m/s (speed of light in vacuum)
  t   = round-trip time (nanoseconds)
  IOR = index of refraction (1.46–1.49 typical)

SMF (G.652): IOR ≈ 1.4677 at 1310nm, 1.4682 at 1550nm
MMF (OM1):  IOR ≈ 1.496 at 850nm
MMF (OM3):  IOR ≈ 1.467 at 850nm</div></div>
<div class="field"><label>Round-trip time (ns) from OTDR</label><input type="number" id="otdr-t" placeholder="e.g. 97.4" oninput="calcOTDR()"></div>
