<!-- DC Loop Qualification -->
<div id="m3-dcqual" class="stab-page">
<div class="grid">
<div class="card">
<h3>DC Loop Qualification — Full Test</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> Before activating DSL, you must verify the copper pair meets minimum requirements. The four key measurements are loop resistance, insulation resistance, pair balance, and absence of foreign voltage. All four must pass.
<div class="mth">Pass thresholds (ADSL2+ service):
  Loop resistance (T-R looped):   ≤ 900 Ω
  Insulation R (T-G, R-G, T-R):  ≥ 1 MΩ (line idle)
  Longitudinal balance (T-G/R-G): ratio ≤ 1.5:1
  Foreign AC voltage:             &lt; 0.5 Vrms
  Foreign DC voltage:             &lt; 1.0 V DC</div></div>
<div class="field"><label>Loop resistance T-R looped (Ω)</label><input type="number" id="dq-lr" placeholder="e.g. 420" oninput="calcDQ()"></div>
