<select id="dq-svc" onchange="calcDQ()">
<option value="adsl2">ADSL2+ (≤900 Ω, ≥1 MΩ IR)</option>
<option value="vdsl17">VDSL2-17a (≤200 Ω, ≥1 MΩ IR)</option>
<option value="pots">POTS / Voice only (≤1700 Ω)</option>
<option value="t1">T1 / DS1 (≤750 Ω)</option>
</select></div>
<div id="dq-result" class="result"></div>
</div>
<div class="card">
<h3>Foreign Voltage Interpretation</h3>
<table class="tbl">
<tr><th>Reading</th><th>Meaning</th><th>Action</th></tr>
<tr><td class="pass">&lt;0.5 Vrms AC</td><td>Normal induced noise</td><td>None</td></tr>
<tr><td class="warn">0.5–5 Vrms AC</td><td>Power line induction</td><td>Check for parallel exposure</td></tr>
<tr><td class="fail">&gt;5 Vrms AC</td><td>Significant power exposure</td><td>Locate and correct before work</td></tr>
<tr><td class="fail">&gt;50 Vrms AC</td><td>Direct power contact risk</td><td>DO NOT WORK — call power co.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="pass">&lt;1V DC</td><td>Normal battery leakage</td><td>None</td></tr>
<tr><td class="warn">1–10V DC</td><td>Partial ground fault</td><td>Investigate before service</td></tr>
<tr><td class="fail">&gt;50V DC</td><td>Direct battery contact</td><td>Hazardous — isolate first</td></tr>
</table>
<div class="divider"></div>
<h3>Balance Ratio Guide</h3>
<div class="eli5">
<strong>Pair balance</strong> = how symmetrically the pair is referenced to ground. Perfect balance = T-G equals R-G. A 2:1 ratio means one conductor has twice the fault to ground as the other.
<div class="mth">Balance ratio = higher_IR / lower_IR
  &lt; 1.5 : Excellent balance
  1.5–3  : Acceptable for DSL
  3–10   : Marginal — may cause noise issues
  &gt; 10   : Poor balance — locate asymmetric fault</div>
</div>
</div>
