<h3>ADSL / ADSL2+ Reach & Speed Estimator</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> ADSL speed drops sharply with distance. The main enemy is insertion loss (signal attenuation at 300 kHz). Loop resistance tells you if the physical copper qualifies; insertion loss tells you what speed you'll get.
<div class="mth">Insertion loss (approx) at 300 kHz for 24 AWG:
  IL ≈ 0.115 × √f_kHz × L_kft   (dB)
  At 300 kHz: IL ≈ 1.99 × L_kft

ADSL2+ speed rough estimate:
  IL &lt; 20 dB:  ~15–20 Mbps down
  IL 20–30 dB: ~8–15 Mbps down
  IL 30–40 dB: ~3–8 Mbps down
  IL 40–50 dB: ~1–3 Mbps down
  IL &gt; 50 dB:  &lt;1 Mbps or no sync</div></div>
