<div class="eli5"><strong>VDSL2 crosstalk (FEXT/NEXT):</strong><br>
Multiple VDSL2 lines in the same cable binder group interfere with each other — called FEXT (far-end crosstalk). This is why VDSL2 speeds in a large binder group can be significantly lower than theoretical maximums. Vectoring (G.993.5) cancels FEXT and restores near-theoretical speeds. Without vectoring, expect 20–40% degradation in a busy binder group.</div>
