<!-- T1 Loop Qualification -->
<div id="m5-t1qual" class="stab-page">
<div class="grid">
<div class="card">
<h3>T1 / DS1 Loop Qualification</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> T1 uses Alternate Mark Inversion (AMI) or B8ZS line coding at 1.544 Mbps. The limiting factor is insertion loss at 772 kHz (the Nyquist frequency for T1). Maximum allowable insertion loss is 22.5 dB from CO to CSU. Beyond that, the repeater or span extender must be used.
<div class="mth">T1 span loss limit:  22.5 dB at 772 kHz
T1 max loop (24 AWG): ~18,000 ft (3.4 miles)
T1 max loop (22 AWG): ~27,000 ft (5.1 miles)
T1 max loop (19 AWG): ~36,000 ft (6.8 miles)

Insertion loss at 772 kHz (approx):
  19 AWG: ~0.63 dB/kft
  22 AWG: ~0.84 dB/kft  
  24 AWG: ~1.25 dB/kft
  26 AWG: ~2.00 dB/kft

LBO (Line Build Out) at DSX/CSU:
  0 dB    = 0–133 ft from DSX
  -7.5 dB = 133–266 ft
  -15 dB  = 266–399 ft
  -22.5 dB = 399–533 ft (max)</div></div>
<div class="field"><label>Cable gauge</label>
<select id="t1-awg" onchange="calcT1()">
<option value="0.63">19 AWG — 0.63 dB/kft</option>
<option value="0.84">22 AWG — 0.84 dB/kft</option>
<option value="1.25" selected>24 AWG — 1.25 dB/kft</option>
<option value="2.00">26 AWG — 2.00 dB/kft</option>
</select></div>
<div class="field"><label>Loop length (feet)</label><input type="number" id="t1-l" placeholder="e.g. 12000" oninput="calcT1()"></div>
