<!-- HDSL / SHDSL -->
<div id="m5-hdsl" class="stab-page">
<div class="grid">
<div class="card">
<h3>HDSL / HDSL2 / SHDSL Reach Estimator</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> HDSL (High-bit-rate DSL) carries T1 (1.544 Mbps) over longer distances than traditional T1 repeatered spans by using a more efficient line code (2B1Q or TC-PAM). No load coils allowed; no bridge taps. HDSL2 uses a single pair; original HDSL needs two pairs.
<div class="mth">HDSL reach limits (24 AWG, 2B1Q):
  Original HDSL (2 pairs): ~24,000 ft (4.55 mi)
  HDSL2 (1 pair):          ~21,000 ft (3.98 mi)
  SHDSL (ITU G.991.2):     ~24,000 ft at 2.3 Mbps
                            ~18,000 ft at 4.6 Mbps

Insertion loss limit:
  HDSL at 196 kHz:  ~28 dB max
  HDSL2 at 392 kHz: ~28 dB max

2B1Q signal levels:
  +3 = +2.5V  |  +1 = +0.833V
  -1 = -0.833V | -3 = -2.5V</div></div>
