<h3>SLC-96 Span Qualification</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> The SLC-96 (Subscriber Loop Carrier 96-channel) is a T-carrier based DLC system. It uses DS1 (T1) spans on the feeder cable from the CO to the remote terminal. Each span carries 24 voice channels. Four spans = 96 channels. The feeder T1 spans must qualify just like any T1 circuit.
<div class="mth">SLC-96 feeder spans: 4 × T1 (DS1) = 96 channels
  Each span: 1.544 Mbps, AMI or B8ZS, 2-wire
  Max feeder span: same as T1 = 22.5 dB @ 772 kHz
  Repeater spacing: 6,000 ft typical
  
Remote terminal power: −48V from CO via power cable
  OR local commercial power with battery backup
  
Signaling: SF (D4) or ESF framing
  ESF preferred — provides CRC-6 error monitoring</div></div>
