<tr><td>Feeder cable</td><td>CO to RT</td><td>4 DS1 spans (8 pairs) in buried/aerial cable</td></tr>
<tr><td>RT (Remote Terminal)</td><td>Pedestal/cabinet</td><td>Demultiplexes DS1s to 96 subscriber pairs</td></tr>
<tr><td>Distribution pairs</td><td>RT to home</td><td>Standard POTS pairs — 24 AWG typical</td></tr>
<tr><td>Power cable</td><td>CO to RT</td><td>−48V DC at up to 5A (CO-powered systems)</td></tr>
</table>
<div class="divider"></div>
<div class="eli5"><strong>SLC-96 troubleshooting tips:</strong><br>
• If all 24 channels on one span fail simultaneously → DS1 span issue, not subscriber problem<br>
• If channels 1–24 fail and 25–96 work → Span 1 DS1 issue<br>
• Single channel failing → subscriber pair or cross-connect issue<br>
• RT alarm (no power) → check feeder power cable and CO power supply<br>
• Span sync loss → check DS1 span loss, connectors, DSX cross-connect</div>
