<!-- T1 Alarm Decoder -->
<div id="m5-t1alarm" class="stab-page">
<div class="grid">
<div class="card">
<h3>T1 / DS1 Alarm Decoder</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> T1 alarms are a built-in signaling system that tells you what's wrong and where. Understanding the alarm hierarchy prevents chasing the wrong end of the circuit.
</div>
<table class="tbl">
<tr><th>Alarm</th><th>Full name</th><th>Meaning</th><th>Look here</th></tr>
<tr><td class="fail">LOS</td><td>Loss of Signal</td><td>No signal received at all — line is dead</td><td>Physical layer: cable, connector, card, power</td></tr>
<tr><td class="fail">LOF</td><td>Loss of Frame</td><td>Signal present but can't find framing pattern</td><td>Framing mismatch (SF vs ESF), bad LBO, high BER</td></tr>
<tr><td class="fail">AIS</td><td>Alarm Indication Signal</td><td>All-ones "blue alarm" — upstream failure, passing it downstream</td><td>Look UPSTREAM from where you see AIS — that's where the real problem is</td></tr>
<tr><td class="warn">RAI / YEL</td><td>Remote Alarm Indication / Yellow</td><td>Far end is receiving LOS or LOF and telling you</td><td>Far-end equipment is seeing a problem — check the OTHER direction</td></tr>
<tr><td class="warn">OOF</td><td>Out of Frame</td><td>Framing errors &gt;2 in 5 — precursor to LOF</td><td>Noise on line, bad cable section, LBO mismatch</td></tr>
<tr><td class="warn">BPV</td><td>Bipolar Violation</td><td>Line code errors — same polarity twice in a row (AMI)</td><td>Bridge tap, noise, repeater problem, LBO</td></tr>
<tr><td class="warn">CRC</td><td>CRC-6 Error (ESF only)</td><td>Frame check sequence errors</td><td>Bit errors anywhere in the span — noise, marginal loss</td></tr>
<tr><td class="warn">ES</td><td>Errored Second</td><td>Any second with at least one error</td><td>Marginal span — trending problem</td></tr>
<tr><td class="fail">SES</td><td>Severely Errored Second</td><td>&gt;320 BPV in a second</td><td>Major span problem — near outage</td></tr>
<tr><td class="fail">UAS</td><td>Unavailable Second</td><td>10+ consecutive SES — circuit down</td><td>Full span failure — escalate</td></tr>
</table>
<div class="divider"></div>
<h3>T1 Alarm Priority / Chase Direction</h3>
<div class="eli5">
<strong>AIS = look upstream. RAI/Yellow = look at the other end.</strong><br><br>
If Equipment A shows AIS: Equipment A is receiving all-ones from Equipment B. Equipment B has declared a failure. Fix B first.<br><br>
If Equipment A shows RAI/Yellow: Equipment B is telling A it has a problem. Equipment A is the one failing — fix A.
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

