<!-- Rectifier AC Load -->
<div id="m6-rect" class="stab-page">
<div class="grid">
<div class="card">
<h3>Single Rectifier DC → AC Load Calculator</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> Rectifiers convert AC power to −48V DC. To size the AC circuit feeding a rectifier, you need to know how much AC current it draws. This depends on the DC output power, rectifier efficiency, power factor, and whether it's single or 3-phase AC input.
<div class="mth">AC input power (single phase):
  P_AC = (V_DC × I_DC) / (η × PF)
  I_AC = P_AC / V_AC
  
  η = rectifier efficiency (0.88–0.93 typical)
  PF = power factor (0.95–0.99 for modern SMPS)

3-phase AC input:
  I_AC_per_phase = P_AC / (√3 × V_LL × PF)
  V_LL = line-to-line voltage (208V or 480V typical)

NEC 125% rule for continuous loads:
  I_breaker_min = I_AC × 1.25</div></div>
