<div class="card">
<h3>PDSC Breaker / Feeder Sizing</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> PDSC (Power Distribution and Switching Center) or equivalent DC power distribution panels route −48V from the main bus to individual equipment BDFBs. Sizing the breakers and feeders correctly prevents nuisance trips and fire hazards.
<div class="mth">Breaker sizing (continuous DC loads):
  I_breaker = I_load × 1.25   (NEC 210.20)
  Round up to next standard breaker size

Standard breaker sizes (A):
  15, 20, 30, 40, 50, 60, 70, 80, 90, 100,
  110, 125, 150, 175, 200, 225, 250, 300,
  350, 400, 450, 500, 600, 700, 800, 1000

Wire sizing: use NEC Table 310.15(B)(16) at 75°C
  For DC: wire ampacity same table — DC is actually
  slightly better than AC (no skin effect)</div></div>
<div class="field"><label>DC load current (A)</label><input type="number" id="pdsc-i" placeholder="e.g. 240" oninput="calcPDSC()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Conductor temperature rating</label>
