<!-- Free-Space Path Loss -->
<div id="m7-fspl" class="stab-page">
<div class="grid">
<div class="card">
<h3>Free-Space Path Loss (FSPL)</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> Radio signals spread out as they travel, just like light from a flashlight. The farther the signal travels, and the higher the frequency, the more it spreads and weakens. FSPL is the theoretical minimum loss on a clear path — real links always have more loss due to atmosphere, obstacles, and antenna imperfections.
<div class="mth">FSPL (dB) = 20×log10(d) + 20×log10(f) + 92.44
  d = distance in km
  f = frequency in GHz

Or in miles/MHz:
  FSPL (dB) = 36.6 + 20×log10(f_MHz) + 20×log10(d_mi)

At 6 GHz, 20 miles:
  FSPL = 20×log10(20×1.609) + 20×log10(6) + 92.44
       = 30.1 + 15.6 + 92.44 = 138.1 dB</div></div>
<div class="field"><label>Frequency (GHz)</label><input type="number" id="fspl-f" placeholder="e.g. 6" step="0.1" oninput="calcFSPL()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Path distance</label><input type="number" id="fspl-d" placeholder="e.g. 20" oninput="calcFSPL()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Distance unit</label>
<select id="fspl-du" onchange="calcFSPL()">
<option value="km">km</option>
<option value="mi" selected>miles</option>
<option value="ft">feet</option>
</select></div>
<div id="fspl-result" class="result"></div>
</div>
<div class="card">
<h3>FSPL Quick Reference</h3>
<table class="tbl">
<tr><th>Band</th><th>Freq</th><th>10 mi</th><th>25 mi</th><th>50 mi</th></tr>
