<!-- Frequency / Wavelength -->
<div id="m7-freq" class="stab-page">
<div class="grid">
<div class="card">
<h3>Frequency ↔ Wavelength Converter</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> Frequency and wavelength are two ways to describe the same wave. Higher frequency = shorter wavelength. Wavelength matters for antenna sizing — a half-wave dipole is exactly λ/2 long.
<div class="mth">λ = c / f
  c = 299,792,458 m/s (speed of light)
  λ = wavelength (meters)
  f = frequency (Hz)

For free space:  λ(m) = 0.3 / f(GHz)
  At 6 GHz:  λ = 0.3/6 = 0.05 m = 5 cm
  At 11 GHz: λ = 0.3/11 = 2.7 cm
  At 2.4 GHz: λ = 0.3/2.4 = 12.5 cm

Half-wave dipole length = λ/2 × 0.95 (velocity factor)</div></div>
<div class="field"><label>Frequency (GHz)</label><input type="number" id="fw-ghz" placeholder="e.g. 6" step="0.001" oninput="fwConv('ghz')"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Frequency (MHz)</label><input type="number" id="fw-mhz" placeholder="e.g. 6000" step="0.1" oninput="fwConv('mhz')"></div>
