<!-- Link Budget -->
<div id="m7-budget" class="stab-page">
<div class="grid">
<div class="card">
<h3>Microwave Link Budget</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> A link budget is a balance sheet for the radio signal. Start with transmit power, add antenna gains, subtract all losses (FSPL, cables, atmospheric, rain), and the result must exceed the receiver's minimum threshold by the required fade margin.
<div class="mth">RSL = P_tx + G_tx − L_tx − FSPL − L_atm − L_rain − L_rx + G_rx
  RSL   = received signal level (dBm)
  P_tx  = transmit power (dBm)
  G_tx  = transmit antenna gain (dBi)
  G_rx  = receive antenna gain (dBi)
  L_tx  = transmit feed/cable loss (dB)
  L_rx  = receive feed/cable loss (dB)
  FSPL  = free-space path loss (dB)
  L_atm = atmospheric absorption (dB)
  L_rain = rain fade (dB)

Fade margin = RSL − receiver threshold (dBm)</div></div>
<div class="field"><label>Transmit power (dBm)</label><input type="number" id="lb-ptx" placeholder="e.g. 23" oninput="calcLB()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Tx antenna gain (dBi)</label><input type="number" id="lb-gtx" placeholder="e.g. 38" oninput="calcLB()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Tx feed/cable loss (dB)</label><input type="number" id="lb-ltx" value="1" step="0.1" oninput="calcLB()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Free-space path loss (dB) — use FSPL tab</label><input type="number" id="lb-fspl" placeholder="e.g. 138" oninput="calcLB()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Atmospheric absorption (dB)</label><input type="number" id="lb-latm" value="0.5" step="0.1" oninput="calcLB()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Rain fade allowance (dB)</label><input type="number" id="lb-lrain" value="0" step="0.1" oninput="calcLB()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Rx feed/cable loss (dB)</label><input type="number" id="lb-lrx" value="1" step="0.1" oninput="calcLB()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Rx antenna gain (dBi)</label><input type="number" id="lb-grx" placeholder="e.g. 38" oninput="calcLB()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Receiver threshold / sensitivity (dBm)</label><input type="number" id="lb-thresh" placeholder="e.g. -80" oninput="calcLB()"></div>
<div id="lb-result" class="result"></div>
</div>
<div class="card">
<h3>Link Budget — Typical Values Reference</h3>
<table class="tbl">
<tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Typical range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
<tr><td>Tx power (microwave)</td><td>+10 to +30 dBm</td><td>Regulated by FCC license</td></tr>
<tr><td>Antenna gain 2-ft dish</td><td>30–33 dBi</td><td>Varies by frequency</td></tr>
<tr><td>Antenna gain 4-ft dish</td><td>36–39 dBi</td><td>Most common long-haul</td></tr>
<tr><td>Antenna gain 6-ft dish</td><td>40–43 dBi</td><td>Used for marginal paths</td></tr>
