<tr><td>Receiver threshold</td><td>−70 to −90 dBm</td><td>Depends on modulation (BPSK vs 1024QAM)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Required fade margin</td><td>30–40 dB</td><td>For 99.999% availability</td></tr>
</table>
<div class="tip">Higher modulation (256QAM, 1024QAM) gives more throughput but requires a better RSL — threshold goes up from −85 dBm (BPSK) to around −60 dBm (1024QAM). Always design for the worst-case modulation you need during rain fades.</div>
