<!-- EIRP -->
<div id="m7-eirp" class="stab-page">
<div class="grid">
<div class="card">
<h3>EIRP Calculator</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> EIRP (Effective Isotropic Radiated Power) is the equivalent power that a perfectly omnidirectional antenna would need to produce the same signal in the direction of maximum gain as your actual antenna+transmitter combination. The FCC licenses microwave links based on EIRP.
<div class="mth">EIRP (dBm) = P_tx (dBm) + G_ant (dBi) − L_feed (dB)
EIRP (W)   = 10^((EIRP_dBm − 30) / 10)

FCC Part 101 EIRP limits (licensed microwave):
  2 GHz band:    55 dBW max (316 kW)
  6 GHz band:    55 dBW max
  11 GHz band:   55 dBW max
  18 GHz band:   55 dBW max
  
Note: dBW = dBm − 30
  0 dBW = 1 W = 30 dBm</div></div>
<div class="field"><label>Transmit power (dBm)</label><input type="number" id="eirp-ptx" placeholder="e.g. 23" oninput="calcEIRP()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Antenna gain (dBi)</label><input type="number" id="eirp-gain" placeholder="e.g. 38" oninput="calcEIRP()"></div>
