<div class="card">
<h3>Beamwidth Reference</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>Narrower beamwidth = higher gain = more pointing precision required.</strong>
<div class="mth">Approx half-power beamwidth:
  BW ≈ 70 × λ / D  (degrees)
  λ = wavelength (m)
  D = dish diameter (m)

At 6 GHz (λ=5cm), 4-ft dish (1.2m):
  BW ≈ 70 × 0.05 / 1.2 = 2.9°

At 23 GHz (λ=1.3cm), 4-ft dish:
  BW ≈ 70 × 0.013 / 1.2 = 0.76°

Rule: 38 GHz with a 4-ft dish has a 0.45° beam.
That's less than 1 degree — alignment is CRITICAL.</div></div>
