<div class="card">
<h3>dBm ↔ Watts ↔ mW Converter</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> dBm is decibels relative to 1 milliwatt. It's a logarithmic scale that makes very large and very small power levels easy to work with. Every +3 dB doubles the power; every +10 dB multiplies by 10.
<div class="mth">dBm = 10 × log10(P_mW)
P_mW = 10^(dBm/10)
P_W  = P_mW / 1000
dBW  = dBm − 30

Quick reference:
  0 dBm  = 1 mW
  10 dBm = 10 mW
  20 dBm = 100 mW = 0.1 W
  23 dBm = 200 mW ≈ typical microwave Tx
  30 dBm = 1 W = 1,000 mW
  40 dBm = 10 W
  43 dBm = 20 W
  50 dBm = 100 W</div></div>
