<!-- Fade Margin -->
<div id="m7-fade" class="stab-page">
<div class="grid">
<div class="card">
<h3>Fade Margin & Availability Estimator</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> Fade margin is the buffer between your received signal level (RSL) and the threshold where the link fails. More margin = better availability. The Barnett-Vigants formula estimates outage time based on fade margin, path length, frequency, and climate roughness factor.
<div class="mth">Barnett-Vigants outage probability:
  P_out = c × f × d³ × 10^(−FM/10)
  
  c  = climate/terrain factor
       6×10⁻⁷ (average inland, smooth terrain)
       1×10⁻⁶ (hilly, humid)
       2×10⁻⁶ (very smooth water/flat coastal)
  f  = frequency (GHz)
  d  = path length (km)
  FM = fade margin (dB)

Availability = 1 − P_out
Outage time per year = P_out × 8760 hours</div></div>
<div class="field"><label>RSL — Received Signal Level (dBm)</label><input type="number" id="fm-rsl" placeholder="e.g. -45" oninput="calcFM()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Receiver threshold (dBm)</label><input type="number" id="fm-thresh" placeholder="e.g. -80" oninput="calcFM()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Frequency (GHz)</label><input type="number" id="fm-f" placeholder="e.g. 6" step="0.1" oninput="calcFM()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Path length (miles)</label><input type="number" id="fm-d" placeholder="e.g. 20" oninput="calcFM()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Climate / terrain factor (c)</label>
<select id="fm-c" onchange="calcFM()">
<option value="6e-7" selected>Average inland / smooth terrain: 6×10⁻⁷</option>
<option value="1e-6">Hilly / humid: 1×10⁻⁶</option>
<option value="2e-6">Very smooth / flat coastal: 2×10⁻⁶</option>
<option value="3e-7">Mountainous / dry: 3×10⁻⁷</option>
</select></div>
<div id="fm-result" class="result"></div>
</div>
<div class="card">
<h3>Availability vs Fade Margin Reference</h3>
<table class="tbl">
