<div class="card">
<h3>dB Quick Reference — 3-6-10 Rule</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> You can do most RF math in your head if you remember these three numbers: +3 dB doubles power, +6 dB quadruples it, +10 dB multiplies by 10. For losses (negative dB), just reverse.
<div class="mth">+3 dB  = ×2.0 power (exactly: ×1.995)
+6 dB  = ×4.0 power
+10 dB = ×10  power

−3 dB  = ÷2   (half power)
−10 dB = ÷10

Examples:
  0 dBm = 1 mW
  +3 dBm = 2 mW   +6 dBm = 4 mW   +10 dBm = 10 mW
  +13 dBm = 20 mW  +16 dBm = 40 mW  +20 dBm = 100 mW
  +23 dBm = 200 mW +30 dBm = 1000 mW = 1 W

Combine: +23 dBm = +20 + 3 = 100 mW × 2 = 200 mW ✓</div></div>
