<h3>Generator Sizing Calculator</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> A generator must be sized to handle the total load plus starting surges. Motors and UPS chargers draw 3–6× rated current at startup. The generator kVA must exceed the total running load with headroom for the largest single motor start.
<div class="mth">Generator sizing steps:
  1. Sum all continuous loads (kW)
  2. Identify largest motor start (kW × 3 for surge)
  3. Account for power factor: kVA = kW / PF
  4. Add 20% safety margin

Generator kVA = (Total_kW + Surge_kW) / PF × 1.2

DC plant sizing (rectifiers = continuous load, PF≈0.97):
  kVA = (V_DC × I_DC / Rectifier_eff) / PF
  Standard rule: 1 kVA per 16A of −48V DC load</div></div>
