<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> How long will the generator run on a tank? Fuel consumption depends on generator size and how hard it's working. A lightly loaded generator burns much less fuel than a fully loaded one.
<div class="mth">Runtime = Tank_gallons / Consumption_gph

Fuel consumption estimate:
  gph ≈ (kW_load × 0.065) for diesel at 75% load
  
More precisely (diesel):
  gph = Rated_kW × Load_% × Heat_rate / HHV_diesel
  Heat rate ≈ 9,000–11,000 BTU/kWh (diesel genset)
  HHV diesel ≈ 137,000 BTU/gallon
  
Simplified rule of thumb:
  ~0.065 gal/hr per kW at 75% load</div></div>
