<!-- CRAC/CRAH Sizing -->
<div id="m9-crac" class="stab-page">
<div class="grid">
<div class="card">
<h3>CRAC / CRAH Unit Sizing</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> CRAC (Computer Room Air Conditioner) units cool the room by circulating air and removing heat. You need to size them to handle the total heat load with N+1 redundancy — if one unit fails, the remaining units handle the full load.
<div class="mth">CFM required per unit:
  CFM = Heat_BTU_hr / (1.08 × ΔT_°F)
  ΔT = supply air temp − return air temp
  Typical ΔT = 15–20°F for CRAC

Tons per unit = Total_tons / (N_units − 1)
  (N+1 redundancy — any one unit can fail)

Sensible heat ratio (SHR):
  Telecom/CO equipment: SHR ≈ 0.95–1.0
  (almost all sensible heat, minimal latent/humidity)
  Office/mixed: SHR ≈ 0.75–0.85</div></div>
<div class="field"><label>Total room heat load (kW)</label><input type="number" id="crac-kw" placeholder="e.g. 50" oninput="calcCRAC()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Number of CRAC units (total installed)</label><input type="number" id="crac-n" value="2" min="1" oninput="calcCRAC()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Supply air temperature (°F)</label><input type="number" id="crac-sup" value="65" oninput="calcCRAC()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Return air temperature (°F)</label><input type="number" id="crac-ret" value="80" oninput="calcCRAC()"></div>
<div id="crac-result" class="result"></div>
</div>
<div class="card">
<h3>Hot/Cold Aisle Layout Best Practices</h3>
<div class="step"><span class="sn">1</span><span class="stxt"><strong>Alternate rack orientations:</strong> Racks face front-to-front (cold aisle) and back-to-back (hot aisle). Cold aisles receive supply air from floor tiles; hot aisles exhaust to ceiling return.</span></div>
<div class="step"><span class="sn">2</span><span class="stxt"><strong>Seal all floor tile openings:</strong> Blanking panels in empty rack units, grommets over unused cable cutouts, and brush strips at cable entry points. Even 10% uncontrolled air bypass can raise inlet temperatures by 5–8°F.</span></div>
<div class="step"><span class="sn">3</span><span class="stxt"><strong>Perforated tile placement:</strong> Tiles should be directly in front of high-density racks. Placing tiles in the hot aisle wastes cooling capacity and short-circuits airflow.</span></div>
<div class="step"><span class="sn">4</span><span class="stxt"><strong>Aisle containment:</strong> Cold aisle containment (doors/ceiling at ends of cold aisle) can reduce cooling energy by 20–40% by preventing cold and hot air mixing.</span></div>
<div class="step"><span class="sn">5</span><span class="stxt"><strong>Monitor inlet temperature:</strong> ASHRAE A1 class equipment allows 64.4–80.6°F (18–27°C) inlet. NEBS long-term max is 104°F (40°C). Place temperature sensors at the front of high-density racks at mid-height.</span></div>
<div class="wbox">The single biggest cooling efficiency mistake in legacy COs is running CRAC units in "cooling mode" with no hot/cold aisle separation. Cold and hot air mix before reaching equipment — the CRAC works twice as hard for half the effect.</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<!-- Floor Loading -->
<div id="m9-floor" class="stab-page">
<div class="grid">
<div class="card">
<h3>Equipment Floor Loading Calculator</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> Heavy equipment like battery strings, large UPS units, and full equipment racks can easily exceed a building's floor load rating. Before installing heavy equipment, calculate the load in pounds per square foot and compare to the structural rating. A standard office floor is typically 50–100 lb/ft². A telecom CO can be 150–300 lb/ft².
<div class="mth">Point load from equipment:
  PSF = Weight_lbs / Footprint_ft²
  
  For equipment on legs/wheels (concentrated loads):
  Effective area per leg = π × r²  (r = leg pad radius)
  Load per leg = Total_weight / Number_of_legs

Spreading with steel plates:
  Effective area = plate_area + (2 × plate_thickness × depth)
  Distributed PSF = Weight / Effective_area</div></div>
<div class="field"><label>Equipment weight (lbs)</label><input type="number" id="fl-w" placeholder="e.g. 3500" oninput="calcFL()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Equipment footprint width (inches)</label><input type="number" id="fl-fw" placeholder="e.g. 24" oninput="calcFL()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Equipment footprint depth (inches)</label><input type="number" id="fl-fd" placeholder="e.g. 36" oninput="calcFL()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Number of legs/feet</label><input type="number" id="fl-legs" value="4" min="1" oninput="calcFL()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Floor rating (lb/ft²)</label><input type="number" id="fl-rating" placeholder="e.g. 150" oninput="calcFL()"></div>
<div id="fl-result" class="result"></div>
</div>
