<!-- ATS Ride-Through -->
<div id="m9-ats" class="stab-page">
<div class="grid">
<div class="card">
<h3>ATS Transfer Time & Battery Ride-Through</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> When utility power fails, the ATS (Automatic Transfer Switch) starts the generator and transfers load. During this window — typically 10–30 seconds — the batteries carry everything. The risk isn't running out of Ah capacity; it's voltage sag from battery internal resistance at high discharge current.
<div class="mth">Ah consumed during transfer:
  Ah = I × (t_seconds / 3600)

Voltage sag estimate:
  V_sag = I × R_internal
  R_int ≈ 0.002 Ω per cell (VRLA new)
  R_int ≈ 0.005 Ω per cell (VRLA aged)
  R_int ≈ 0.001 Ω per cell (flooded new)

For 24-cell (−48V) string at 320A:
  V_sag = 320 × (24 × 0.002) = 15.4V
  Bus: 52 − 15.4 = 36.6V → LOW VOLTAGE ALARM!</div></div>
<div class="field"><label>Plant load during transfer (A)</label><input type="number" id="ats-i" placeholder="e.g. 280" oninput="calcATS9()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Battery capacity (Ah per string)</label><input type="number" id="ats-ah" placeholder="e.g. 400" oninput="calcATS9()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Number of strings</label><input type="number" id="ats-str" value="2" min="1" oninput="calcATS9()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>ATS transfer time</label>
<select id="ats-t" onchange="calcATS9()">
<option value="10">Fast-start diesel — 10 sec</option>
<option value="20" selected>Standard diesel — 20 sec</option>
<option value="30">Natural gas / propane — 30 sec</option>
<option value="60">Manual transfer — 60 sec</option>
</select></div>
<div class="field"><label>Battery internal resistance type</label>
<select id="ats-rint" onchange="calcATS9()">
<option value="0.002">VRLA / AGM (new) — 0.002 Ω/cell</option>
<option value="0.005" selected>VRLA / AGM (aged) — 0.005 Ω/cell</option>
<option value="0.001">Flooded (new) — 0.001 Ω/cell</option>
<option value="0.003">Flooded (aged) — 0.003 Ω/cell</option>
</select></div>
<div id="ats-result" class="result"></div>
</div>
<div class="card">
