<!-- Voltage Drop -->
<div id="m10-vdrop" class="stab-page">
<div class="grid">
<div class="card">
<h3>Voltage Drop AC/DC Calculator</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> Voltage drop is the loss of voltage as current flows through a conductor. NEC recommends keeping voltage drop under 3% on branch circuits and 5% total (feeder + branch). For DC power wiring in a CO, keep drops under 1.5V total.
<div class="mth">Single phase AC / DC:
  V_drop = 2 × L × R_per_unit × I   (2-wire: out + back)
  
Three phase AC:
  V_drop = √3 × L × R_per_unit × I × PF

V_drop% = (V_drop / V_source) × 100

NEC recommendation: ≤3% on branch circuits</div></div>
