<!-- Load Coils -->
<div id="m10-loadcoil" class="stab-page">
<div class="grid">
<div class="card">
<h3>H88 Load Coil Location Calculator</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> Load coils are inductors spliced into long telephone cables to boost voice frequency response. They're great for voice calls on long loops but completely block DSL and T1. H88 loading means the first coil is at 3,000 ft from the CO and subsequent coils are every 6,000 ft.
<div class="mth">H88 loading scheme positions:
  1st coil:  3,000 ft from CO
  2nd coil:  9,000 ft  (3,000 + 6,000)
  3rd coil:  15,000 ft (3,000 + 12,000)
  4th coil:  21,000 ft
  5th coil:  27,000 ft
  ...nth coil: 3,000 + (n-1) × 6,000 ft

D66 loading: 1st at 2,000 ft, every 4,000 ft
B88 loading: 1st at 3,000 ft, every 4,500 ft</div></div>
<div class="field"><label>Customer loop length (feet)</label><input type="number" id="lc-l" placeholder="e.g. 18000" oninput="calcLC()"></div>
<div class="field"><label>Loading scheme</label>
<select id="lc-scheme" onchange="calcLC()">
<option value="H88">H88 — first 3000, spacing 6000 ft</option>
<option value="D66">D66 — first 2000, spacing 4000 ft</option>
<option value="B88">B88 — first 3000, spacing 4500 ft</option>
</select></div>
<div id="lc-result" class="result"></div>
</div>
<div class="card">
<h3>Load Coil Identification Guide</h3>
<table class="tbl">
<tr><th>Symptom</th><th>Evidence of load coil</th></tr>
<tr><td>DSL won't train on long loop</td><td>Check loop length — if &gt;12,000 ft, suspect coil</td></tr>
<tr><td>TDR shows impedance bump</td><td>Coil shows as high impedance event at expected distance</td></tr>
<tr><td>ADSL modem shows very high attenuation, no sync</td><td>Coil blocks 26 kHz+ frequencies completely</td></tr>
<tr><td>Voice perfect but no DSL anywhere</td><td>Classic sign of loaded pair</td></tr>
<tr><td>Loop R is low but DSL fails</td><td>Low resistance doesn't rule out coils — check records</td></tr>
</table>
<div class="divider"></div>
<h3>Load Coil Inductance Values</h3>
<table class="tbl">
<tr><th>Code</th><th>Inductance</th><th>Application</th></tr>
<tr><td>H</td><td>88 mH</td><td>Loaded pairs (most common)</td></tr>
<tr><td>D</td><td>44 mH</td><td>Shorter spacing</td></tr>
<tr><td>B</td><td>88 mH</td><td>Different spacing than H</td></tr>
</table>
<div class="wbox">Load coils must be physically removed — there is no software fix. Each coil is a discrete component inside a splice case or loading coil case. Removal requires a technician to locate and open each coil point. On a 3-coil loop (18,000 ft), this is a significant outside plant job.</div>
