<!-- ISDN BRI/PRI -->
<div id="m10-isdn" class="stab-page">
<div class="grid">
<div class="card">
<h3>ISDN BRI Loop Qualification</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> ISDN BRI (Basic Rate Interface) provides 2B+D over a single copper pair. It uses 2B1Q line code at 160 kbps. Loop requirements are similar to but slightly less strict than T1. No load coils, no bridge taps.
<div class="mth">ISDN BRI (2B1Q) loop limits:
  Max loop resistance:  ~1,300 Ω (total loop)
  Max loop length:      ~18,000 ft (24 AWG)
  Insertion loss limit: ~42 dB at 40 kHz
  No load coils allowed
  No bridge taps (&gt;200 ft)

BRI channel structure:
  B1 channel: 64 kbps bearer
  B2 channel: 64 kbps bearer
  D channel:  16 kbps signaling
  Total: 144 kbps payload + framing = 160 kbps</div></div>
<div class="field"><label>Cable gauge</label>
<select id="isdn-awg" onchange="calcISDN()">
<option value="24" selected>24 AWG</option>
<option value="22">22 AWG</option>
<option value="26">26 AWG</option>
</select></div>
<div class="field"><label>Loop length (feet)</label><input type="number" id="isdn-l" placeholder="e.g. 12000" oninput="calcISDN()"></div>
<div id="isdn-result" class="result"></div>
<div class="divider"></div>
<h3>ISDN PRI Reference</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ISDN PRI (Primary Rate Interface) = T1 carrying 23B+D channels. It IS a T1 span from the loop perspective — qualify it exactly like T1 (22.5 dB at 772 kHz limit, no load coils, remove bridge taps).</strong>
<div class="mth">PRI channel structure (T1 North America):
  23 × 64 kbps B channels
  1  × 64 kbps D channel (signaling)
  Total: 24 × 64 kbps = 1.536 Mbps + 8 kbps framing
  
E1 PRI (Europe/International):
  30 × 64 kbps B channels
  1  × 64 kbps D channel
  1  × framing channel
  Total: 32 × 64 kbps = 2.048 Mbps</div></div>
</div>
<div class="card">
<h3>ISDN / BRI Troubleshooting</h3>
<table class="tbl">
<tr><th>Symptom</th><th>Likely cause</th><th>Check</th></tr>
<tr><td>Layer 1 not active</td><td>Physical layer — loop problem</td><td>Loop R, IR, voltage, TDR</td></tr>
<tr><td>Layer 2 not active</td><td>TE/NT mismatch, provisioning error</td><td>Verify NT1 polarity, SPID settings</td></tr>
<tr><td>One B channel fails</td><td>Cross-connect issue, card provisioning</td><td>Check CO switch programming</td></tr>
<tr><td>Sporadic layer 1 drops</td><td>Marginal loop, noise, poor connection</td><td>Measure insertion loss, check all connectors</td></tr>
<tr><td>No dialtone on analog port of NT1</td><td>NT1 or TA power, provisioning</td><td>Check terminal adapter, SPID setup</td></tr>
</table>
