<!-- Lightning Protection -->
<div id="m10-lightning" class="stab-page">
<div class="grid">
<div class="card">
<h3>Lightning Protection — Zone of Protection</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> The rolling sphere model defines a "cone of protection" around a lightning rod. Any object within the sphere's protected zone is shielded from direct lightning strikes. The sphere radius is 150 feet (45m) for Class I (most telecom structures).
<div class="mth">Rolling sphere radius:
  Class I (general structures): R = 150 ft (45m)
  Class II (structures &lt;75 ft):  R = 100 ft (30m)
  
Protected zone geometry:
  For a mast of height h:
  Horizontal protected radius at ground level:
  r = √(R² − (R−h)²) = √(2Rh − h²)  (h ≤ R)
  
  At h = 50 ft mast, R = 150 ft:
  r = √(2×150×50 − 50²) = √(12,500) = 111.8 ft</div></div>
