<div class="eli5"><strong>eCPRI vs CPRI backhaul:</strong><br>
CPRI (legacy 4G fronthaul) requires 10–25 Gbps even for modest RF bandwidth — it carries raw I/Q samples. eCPRI (enhanced CPRI, used in 5G) uses Ethernet and is much more bandwidth-efficient. A 200 MHz 5G NR cell needs ~10 Gbps eCPRI vs 50+ Gbps CPRI for equivalent capacity.<br><br>
<strong>Fiber requirements for 5G dense deployment:</strong> Each small cell node requires a dedicated fiber path — shared fiber with passive splitters generally can't meet the latency requirements for fronthaul. Planning for 5G densification means planning for significantly increased fiber infrastructure.</div>
