<div class="card">
<h3>Fluke Sidekick / Sidekick VIP — DSL Test Set</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>ELI5:</strong> The Sidekick is a dedicated copper/DSL test set that goes far beyond a DMM. It measures loop resistance, insulation resistance, balance, noise floor, and can run a complete DSL qualification. The VIP model adds impulse noise testing and simultaneous voice/DSL measurement.
</div>
<div class="step"><span class="sn">1</span><span class="stxt"><strong>Autotest sequence:</strong> Connect to the pair at the NID or CO cross-connect. Select Autotest. The Sidekick runs: DC voltage → AC voltage → resistance → IR → capacitance → noise → balance in sequence. Takes ~90 seconds. Full qualification without manual test selection.</span></div>
<div class="step"><span class="sn">2</span><span class="stxt"><strong>3-lead connection for IR:</strong> Sidekick requires Red (+/Tip), Black (−/Ring), and Green (Ground). The ground lead is essential for insulation resistance — T-G and R-G tests require a true earth reference. Without green connected, IR tests are invalid.</span></div>
<div class="step"><span class="sn">3</span><span class="stxt"><strong>Impulse noise test (VIP):</strong> Select Impulse Noise from the menu. Set threshold (−35 dBrn typical for ADSL) and count window (1 minute). Counts impulse events above threshold. ADSL2+ requires &lt;4 impulses/minute above −35 dBrn for reliable service.</span></div>
<div class="step"><span class="sn">4</span><span class="stxt"><strong>DSL qualification mode:</strong> Select DSL Qualification. The Sidekick acts as a modem simulation and estimates achievable sync rate based on measured loop parameters. Compare to expected speed from the line length.</span></div>
