<h3>VIAVI T-BERD / MTS-8000 — Platform Overview</h3>
<div class="eli5"><strong>The T-BERD is a modular platform — different plug-in modules test different things. A single T-BERD chassis can test OTDR, BERT (bit error rate), Ethernet RFC 2544, DS1/T1, OTN, and more. Know which module you have installed.</strong></div>
<div class="step"><span class="sn">1</span><span class="stxt"><strong>OTDR module:</strong> Same workflow as any OTDR — set wavelength, IOR, range, pulse width, averaging. The T-BERD adds SmartTest automated analysis that labels events and flags problems automatically.</span></div>
<div class="step"><span class="sn">2</span><span class="stxt"><strong>RFC 2544 throughput test (Ethernet):</strong> Used for Ethernet service turn-up verification. Tests throughput, frame loss, latency, and back-to-back frames. Customer SLAs are often defined around RFC 2544 results. Connect to both ends simultaneously or use loopback at far end.</span></div>
<div class="step"><span class="sn">3</span><span class="stxt"><strong>BERT (Bit Error Rate Test):</strong> For DS1/T1 and transport verification. Sends a pseudo-random bit pattern (PRBS) through the circuit and counts bit errors. A good circuit shows 0 errors. Any errors indicate a span problem.</span></div>
<div class="step"><span class="sn">4</span><span class="stxt"><strong>Alarm monitor mode:</strong> Leaves the T-BERD connected to a live DS1 circuit in monitoring mode. Logs all alarms (LOS, LOF, AIS, RAI, BPV) with timestamps over time. Invaluable for intermittent problems — connect and leave overnight.</span></div>
